christendom

summary


Jesus of Nazareth is the center of Christianity, He is the incarnation of God, has two natures, He is both the true God and the true man, this is confirmed in Council of Chalcedon in 451.

There are 4 places for Jesus Christ, one is a historical place, to put Jesus Christ in the starting point of Christianity, other three are theological places: He is the One who revealed God, the One who bore salvation, and the One who prescribed the form of a believer's life.

In the historical place, those thinkers of enlightenment thought Jesus Christ brought nothing new, but recovered the natural religion, and all his followers, including Paul modified that quickly. And in the opinion of rationalists, there is nothing good and new in Jesus Christ. However, according to Ritschl, Jesus brought us a new relationship with God.

When Jesus as the One who revealed God, He is seen as the presence of God, became the center of Christianity. We think about Jesus Christ as thinking about God, and He is the Lord, God Himself.

When Jesus is the one who bore the salvation, that means His life, death, and resurrection, those are the base of our salvation. When we say "Jesus made salvation possible", this does not mean there are no other methods to approach salvation. However, according to the traditional opinion, there is only one Base of salvation, only Jesus.

When Jesus is the one who prescribed the form of a believer's life, we can observe the form in the New Testament, to follow Jesus is such a lifestyle.

The titles of Jesus will help us to understand His identification. The first title is Messiah, which means Christ in English. Messiah is the pronunciation of a Hebrew word which means the "one who is anointed", and was translated as Christos in Greek.

Although there are three roles that will be anointed, including prophet, priest, and king, the king was especially suitable for this title. When someone is anointed, that means God elected him and entrusted the duty of a king. Someone's claim Messiah is a godly man, and someone's claim that Messiah is just a human.

There are 4 statements about Jesus as Messiah: 1.Jesus is a political liberator to gather His people to defeat the Romans. 2.Jesus forbade his followers to call his Messiah, this is for the next coming. 3.Although Jesus thinks Himself as Messiah, He is not a political Messiah. 4.Jesus is the Messiah with suffering, not suitable for the hope of Israelite.

The second title of Jesus is the "Son of God". There are many such words in the Old Testament, which means "belong to God". Sometimes, this word is describing the people of Israel, sometimes, this word is describing the king David and his heirs.

"Son of God" was also used to describe the believers of Jesus Christ, according to Paul, Jesus is the own Son of God, we are the adopted son of God. The word "son" is not used to stress the sexual difference, but to stress the right of inheritance, both man and woman who believes in Jesus.

The third title of Jesus is the "son of man". This word is used in the Old Testament for 3 meanings: 1.the title of prophet Ezekiel; 2.the one who brings the last judgment of God, which means he is an apocalyptic role; 3.and the humble creature compared with the angels of God.

In the above three meanings of the "son of man", the third meaning is the suitable explanation for Jesus, however, many scholars are concerned about the second meaning: an apocalyptic role. Jesus has said about the "Son of Man", they think Jesus was saying about another one, but in the early church, they combined the word "Jesus" and "Son of Man" as one.

The fourth title of Jesus is "the Lord", this word occurred many times in the New Testament. The word of "the Lord" is very special for Jews, because they translated the name of God in Hebrew(יהוה) to the Greek word kyrios(κυριός), which is called Tetragrammaton in English. For this reason, they refused to call the Emperor of Rome "lord", and this word to describe Jesus also means Jesus is God.

The fifth title of Jesus is "Savior", when the name of Jesus given by an angel the meaning of His name was revealed by that angel, "He who shall save his people from their sins". In the Old Testament, the only one Savior is God, thus, when Jesus was called "Savior", that means, He is God.

The sixth title of Jesus is "God", John said the "Word is God", and Thomas said "My Lord and my God", moreover, in the book of Hebrews, the author said Jesus is God according to Psalm. However, in Jewish background, there is only One God, thus, Jesus is the one who does the duty of God, such as saving humans, receiving worship, and revealing God.

One theory of the personality of Jesus Christ called "Docetism", from the Greek word "dokeo", which means "seem", "look like". The theory of Docetism is an important doctrine in Gnosticism, which said the body of Christ was not human but a phantasm or a celestial substance, thus the sufferings of Christ were only apparent.






